reviews.text:
Bracknell Railway 🛤 Station 🚉 is a very handy place to use, as you can get a train 🚉 from Bracknell to Reading, all the way through to London Waterloo Station 🚉..
It has disabled ♿ people entrences & parking 🅿.

Usual town train station. There's 3 machines to buy tickets and information screens around.
You may only enter the station from the North side where you'll arrive at the platform that goes to London, there's a pedestrian overpass inside (with lift) to get to trains heading to Reading

Great station in terms of functionality, however the atmosphere can be quite dark and almost feel like a crime is about to happen. The station is kept in satisfactory condition, being reasonably clean. Staff are also very nice and helpful, if they’re ever needed. However, on many occasions they haven’t been exactly ‘on show’ and sometimes sit in their office.

This station does the job for getting from A to B, but don’t expect a glamorous welcome when you arrive.

The station was refurbished a while ago to include step free access via lifts which is nice. Only two trains an hour outside of the peak so you can expect trains to be very busy here. Ticket facilities are sub par at best.
